  "description": [
    "Of these coasts and thus disturb the flanks of the enemy who occupy them The Greek government has declared a separate province the Island of Eubea which hitherto formed an integral part of Eastern Greece A local junta has in consequence been installed to admi nister immediately to its particular wants Theoclitus Pharmacide who has been placed at the head of the junta is an ecclesiastic distinguished by his intellk gene and his energy he resided a long time at Vienna as Archimandrite of the Greek church of that city and managed the Literary Journal called the Greek Mercury Two of the most enterprising Chiefs have also been sent to arrange the military organization of the Island By their activity they have succeeded in drawing from inaction those of the islan ders who residing in the environs of the fortress of Negropont had not hi therto taken an active part This fortress which had not hitherto been seriously besieged is now strictly blockaded As it is not well provisioned and as the nu merous Turks who inhabit it consume much it is hoped its resistance will not be long DOMESTIC CIRCULAR General Post Office July 7 1823 5 The Postmaster"
